                "description": "Actor Madiha Imam recalled a funny yet terrifying experience of doing a live show during the earthquake. The newlywed actor was recently spotted at a chat show on a private news channel when she shared her ordeal of witnessing tremors while shooting for the show. Watch ARY News live on live.arynews.tv “No one actually bothered to […]",
                "content": "Actor Madiha Imam recalled a funny yet terrifying experience of doing a live show during the earthquake. The newlywed actor was recently spotted at a chat show on a private news channel when she shared her ordeal of witnessing tremors while shooting for the show. Watch ARY News live on live.arynews.tv “No one actually bothered to inform me about the earthquake and I continued with the show as usual,” Imam shared with the host. “I was going for a break, and doing everything [as per usual]; [when even] cinematographer and director left and I was the only one sitting at the studio, wondering ‘Where did they go?’,” the actor detailed. A post shared by Syeda Madiha Imam (@madihaimam) “After some time when it ended and everyone came back, they were like ‘You are still here?’,” she quipped flaunting her professionalism. At another point, Imam recalled a funny fan encounter who had dropped flowers for her in the hospital where her father was admitted after meeting with an incident. “My father thought that we have brought flowers for him, so I didn’t tell him the truth,” Imam said. Madiha Imam wipes her Instagram after marriage It is pertinent to mention that the actor recently tied the knot with Moji Basar. She took to her account on the photo and video-sharing application to share the good news with her well-wishers along with some glimpses from the private ceremony. A post shared by Syeda Madiha Imam (@madihaimam) Meanwhile, on the work front, Madiha Imam started off her career as a VJ and soon paved her way to TV. Her notable projects include serials like ‘Mujhay Vida Kar’ , ‘Dushman-e-Jaan’ and ‘Zakham’ as well as her debut Bollywood film ‘Dear Maya’ (2017).",
